==English==
===Etymology===
From the Sanskrit ''[[satī]]'' (lit. ''devoted woman''), from the fem. ''[[sat]]'' (''true, good''). Entered into English in 1786 (during the British control of [[India]]).
===Noun===
'''suttee'''
# The custom and/or act of a Hindu woman giving herself up to be cremated on her husband's funeral pyre as a sign of her devotion to her late spouse.
